1 (1) receivership or bankruptcy of the business entity on whose behalf the
2 license was issued occurs and a license transfer is not requested, with the refund issued for
3 the benefit of the creditors of the license holder;
4 (2) the license holder dies, with the refund issued for the benefit of the
5 estate of the deceased license holder;
6 (3) the license holder volunteers for or has been called into the [armed
7 forces of the United States] UNIFORMED SERVICES or the organized State militia;
8 (4) the license holder surrenders a license and obtains a new license of
9 another class carrying a higher fee, with the refund deducted from the higher fee;
10 (5) the license holder, against whom charges are pending when the license
11 is renewed, is found guilty and the license is revoked, with the refund issued to the license
12 holder in an amount based on the date that the revocation becomes final;
13 (6) the issuance of a license by the Executive Director is reversed on
14 judicial review and the operation of the establishment is prohibited, with the refund issued
15 to the license holder in an amount based on the date that the refusal to grant the renewal
16 becomes final; or
17 (7) the licensed premises is taken by the federal government, the State, or
18 a municipality for public use.
19 4–113.
20 (a) Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, a license holder is not
21 entitled to a refund of the unearned portion of the license fee.
22 (b) A refund shall be issued to a license holder on surrender of the license if:
23 (1) receivership or bankruptcy of the business entity on whose behalf the
24 license was issued occurs and a license transfer is not requested, with the refund issued for
25 the benefit of the creditors of the license holder;
26 (2) the license holder dies, with the refund issued for the benefit of the
27 estate of the deceased license holder;
28 (3) the license holder volunteers for or has been called into the [armed
29 forces of the United States] UNIFORMED SERVICES or the organized State militia;
30 (4) the license holder surrenders a license and obtains a new license of
31 another class carrying a higher fee, with the refund deducted from the higher fee;

SENATE BILL 13 3
1 (5) a license holder, against whom charges are pending when the license is
2 renewed, is found guilty and the license is revoked, with the refund issued to the license
3 holder in an amount based on the date that the revocation becomes final;
4 (6) the issuance of a license by a local licensing board is reversed on judicial
5 review and the operation of the establishment is prohibited, with the refund issued to the
6 license holder in an amount based on the date that the refusal to grant the renewal becomes
7 final; or
8 (7) the licensed premises are taken by the federal government, the State,
9 or a municipality for public use.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
11 1, 2026.
